#!/usr/bin/python
"""You can see the description of the task using the code specified in the title on letcode.

This assignment stumped me because it requires using the group concatenation function, which I didn't know about, but now I know.
Unfortunately, it doesnâ€™t occur to me how you can solve the task without it.

"""

SELECT sell_date, COUNT(DISTINCT product) as num_sold,
GROUP_CONCAT(DISTINCT product ORDER BY product) AS products
FROM Activities
GROUP BY sell_date
ORDER BY sell_date
